//axhrb_regime
{rbrr_regime}

This regime specifies variables that define repository-wide configuration and installation-wide settings within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each
{rbrr_regime}
instance represents foundational infrastructure configuration that rarely changes and is shared across all Recipe Bottle operations.
RBRR assignment files are found in the operator's local filesystem (typically `../station-files/rbrr.env`) and configure the depot identity tuple `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)` (from which depot project ID, GAR repository, pool stem, and bucket fall out as RBDC constants), regional settings, and service account credential file paths.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_resource_prefixing}

Operator-chosen identifiers that scope resource names across the cloud and local-runtime namespaces.
Enables multi-regime isolation on shared infrastructure — distinct depots or developers can coexist in the same GCP project or on the same developer workstation without name collisions.
All three variables must be populated — the marshal-zero path blanks them so a fresh regime requires an explicit operator decision before `rbrr_validate` passes.
The two prefixes must be 2–11 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and end with a hyphen (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9-]*-$`).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_cloud_prefix}

Prefix prepended to all cloud-visible resource names under the depot: GAR image paths, vessel package names,
{gcb_service}
substitutions, and other GCP-scoped identifiers.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_depot_moniker}

Stem identifier that combines with
{rbrr_cloud_prefix}
to form the depot identity tuple.
Must be 1–26 characters, start with a lowercase letter, and contain only lowercase alphanumerics (regex `^[a-z][a-z0-9]*$`).
The tuple derives `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`, `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`, `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`, and `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET` at kindle time.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_runtime_prefix}

Prefix prepended to machine-local resource names: container names, Docker network names, and other runtime identifiers on the operator's workstation.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrr_gcp_region}

The default
{gcp_service}
region for regional services like
{gar_service}
and
{gcb_service}.
Applied when creating repositories and submitting builds unless overridden by operation-specific configuration.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_service_accounts}

Credential file paths derived from a single enrolled directory for each operational role.
Each RBRA file contains the minimum identity and signing material needed for authentication to
{gcp_service}
via service account.
The payor RBRO file contains OAuth refresh credentials for
{rbtr_payor}
operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_secrets_dir}

Directory on the operator's local filesystem outside the source repository that contains all credential files.
Enrolled and validated to exist; individual file paths are derived from this directory at lock time.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_retriever_rbra_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `retriever/rbra.env`.
Enables the operator to assume the retriever role for container image operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_director_rbra_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `director/rbra.env`.
Enables the operator to assume the director role for build submission and image management operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_governor_rbra_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `governor/rbra.env`.
Enables the operator to assume the governor role for
{gcp_project_id}
administration operations.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_payor_rbro_file}

Path derived from
{rbrr_secrets_dir}
as `payor/rbro.env`.
Enables the operator to perform
{rbtr_payor}
OAuth operations using locally stored refresh credentials.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_container_runtime}

Variables that configure container runtime and deployment environment settings.
These settings control DNS resolution and vessel directory layout.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_vessel_dir}

Directory path containing vessel configuration subdirectories.
Each subdirectory defines a vessel image source (bind or conjure mode).

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_dns_server}

DNS server IP address used by sentry containers for name resolution.
Injected into container environment to control DNS behavior.

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_build_configuration}

Operator-chosen
{gcb_service}
build parameters.
Builder images are sourced from the reliquary;
platform targets and VM supply chain are in the
{rbrm_regime}.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}

Compute Engine machine type for the private worker pool, consumed at pool creation time by
{rbtgo_depot_levy}.
Valid families: `e2`, `n2d`, `c3`.
Examples: `e2-standard-2`, `e2-highcpu-8`, `n2d-standard-4`.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_gcb_min_concurrent_builds}

Minimum number of concurrent Cloud Build executions required.
With private pools, the relevant quota metric is `concurrent_private_pool_build_cpus` on the pool's host project.
Machine type is determined by the pool configuration at creation time, not by individual build requests.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_gcb_timeout}

Maximum duration for Cloud Build operations before timeout.
Specified in seconds or duration format (e.g., `3600s`).

//axhrgb_group
{rbrr_group_public_docs}

Public documentation URL for user-facing references.

//axhrgv_variable
{rbrr_public_docs_url}

Complete URL for the public documentation entry point.
Updated per-release (swap branch name) or per-incorporation (point at a fork).
Used by buh_tlt glossary links and user-facing output.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Kindles the {rbrr_regime} fields by enrolling each field with its type-specific constraints under named groups.
Detects unexpected RBRR_ variables.
Composes the docker environment injection set and locks the regime against further modification.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

Validates enrolled fields against type-specific constraints from enrollment.
Validates directory existence for {rbrr_vessel_dir} and {rbrr_secrets_dir}.
Enforces format constraints on {rbrr_cloud_prefix} and {rbrr_depot_moniker}, and the joint-length cap on `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (≤30 chars per the GCP project ID limit).

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders the {rbrr_regime} grouped by section with presentation gates per group.
Sections: Resource Prefixing, Vessel and Local Configuration, GCP Infrastructure, Google Cloud Build Configuration, Secrets Directory, Public Docs.

//axhrb_regime
{rbrp_regime}

This regime specifies variables that define administrative payor configuration within the Recipe Bottle system.
Each
{rbrp_regime}
instance represents the administrative control plane that creates and manages depot projects, links billing accounts, and configures OAuth authentication.
RBRP assignment files are found at the project root (`rbrp.env`) and configure payor project identification, billing account linkage, and OAuth client settings.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrp_payor_project_id}

The GCP project ID hosting the OAuth 2.0 client configuration for payor operations.
Must match the global payor project naming pattern.
Required; regex-validated against RBGC_GLOBAL_PAYOR_REGEX.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrp_billing_account_id}

GCP billing account identifier linked to newly created depot projects.
Optional during initial setup; format XXXXXX-XXXXXX-XXXXXX when present.

//axhrv_variable
{rbrp_oauth_client_id}

Public OAuth 2.0 client identifier for the payor desktop application.
Optional during initial setup; must end with `.apps.googleusercontent.com` when present.

//axhro_kindle
{rbkro_kindle}

Requires RBGC to be kindled first (uses RBGC_GLOBAL_PAYOR_REGEX for validation).
Validates RBRP_PAYOR_PROJECT_ID presence and format.
Validates RBRP_BILLING_ACCOUNT_ID format when present.
Validates RBRP_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID format when present.

//axhro_validate
{rbkro_validate}

RBRP kindle performs validation inline — no separate validate_fields function.
The kindle function is the validator for this regime.

//axhro_render
{rbkro_render}

Renders via rbcr_* shared module.
Sections: Payor Project Identity, Billing Configuration, OAuth Configuration.
Validates after full render completes.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_levy}

NOTE: This operation creates an
{rbtgi_depot}
- a cohesive unit of Recipe Bottle infrastructure including the depot project, build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool
that share their productive lifecycle.

The
{rbtr_payor}
creates a new depot infrastructure from the
{rbtgi_payor_project}.
The operation accepts no CLI parameters; depot identity is read from the kindled regime as `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_payor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}

//axhos_step
. *Validate region against Artifact Registry locations*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations/list[locations.list] for the authenticated project
.. {rbbc_require}
`{rbrr_gcp_region}` present in the returned location set

//axhos_step
. *Derive Depot Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«WORKER_POOL_STEM»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-pool` (resolved by `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_BUCKET»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}b-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET`)
.. NOTE: Joint length `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}` + `d-` + `${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` ≤ 30 chars (GCP project ID limit) is enforced upstream by `zrbrr_enforce` at regime kindle time, so this step performs no length validation.

//axhos_step
. *Create Depot Project*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/create[projects.create] with:
... projectId: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... displayName: `«RBGC_DEPOT_DISPLAY_PREFIX» «RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... NOTE: This displayName prefix anchors CRM v3 search-based depot discrimination used by {rbtgo_depot_list}.
... parent: `{rbrp_parent_type}s/{rbrp_parent_id}` (if parent_type != `none`)
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. {rbbc_require}
project creation successful
.. NOTE: Project name collision against the GCP soft-delete graveyard surfaces here as fatal — re-using a moniker after `{rbtgo_depot_unmake}` requires waiting out the 30-day retention window. The operator-visible "fails if exists" property is intentional under the (CLOUD_PREFIX, MONIKER) shape.

//axhos_step
. *Link Billing Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/billing/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects/updateBillingInfo[cloudbilling.projects.updateBillingInfo] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. Set billingAccountName: `billingAccounts/{rbrp_billing_account_id}`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming billing linkage

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.name` field (CRM v3 returns `projects/{number}`)
.. {rbbc_require}
valid numeric project number after extracting from name

//axhos_step
. *Enable Depot Project APIs*:
.. For each service in [`artifactregistry`, `cloudbuild`, `containeranalysis`, `iam`, `serviceusage`, `storage`]:
... Execute
{rbtoe_api_enable}
with service name and `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_require}
all APIs enabled successfully

//axhos_step
. *Create Private Worker Pools*:
.. For each worker pool variant in [`tether`, `airgap`]:
... {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.workerPools/create[workerPools.create] with:
.... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.... workerPoolId: `«WORKER_POOL_STEM»-«VARIANT»`
.... body for `tether`:
+
----
{
  "privatePoolV1Config": {
    "workerConfig": {
      "machineType": "«RBRR_GCB_MACHINE_TYPE»"
    }
  }
}
----
.... body for `airgap`:
+
----
{
  "privatePoolV1Config": {
    "workerConfig": {
      "machineType": "«RBRR_GCB_MACHINE_TYPE»"
    },
    "networkConfig": {
      "egressOption": "NO_PUBLIC_EGRESS"
    }
  }
}
----
... {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. NOTE:
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}
is a Compute Engine machine type (e.g., `e2-standard-2`), consumed at pool creation time.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.
.. NOTE: The two variants differ only in egress posture. The `airgap` body declares `networkConfig.egressOption: NO_PUBLIC_EGRESS`, which Cloud Build enforces at pool level — builds routed through the airgap pool cannot reach the public internet regardless of build configuration. Awaiting the LRO terminal state at create time surfaces machine-type quota denial here rather than as a downstream "workerpool not found" at the subsequent per-pool probe submission step.

//axhos_step
. *Verify IAM Propagation*:
.. NOTE: After API enablement, IAM permissions may not be immediately available due to eventual consistency.
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/list[artifactregistry.repositories.list] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` in `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until HTTP 200 or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming IAM propagation complete
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "IAM propagation timeout - artifactregistry API not accessible"
.. NOTE: This poll gates the project-scope artifactregistry API surface, not the per-repository resource-scope IAM cache.  Resource-scope cache lag (class C, see <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>) is absorbed in-band by the IAM grant harness when {rbtgo_director_invest} subsequently issues `getIamPolicy` against the AR repo — not by this preflight poll.

//axhos_step
. *Create Build Bucket*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/insert[storage.buckets.insert] with:
... name: `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... lifecycle rule: delete objects after 1 day

//axhos_step
. *Create Container Repository*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/create[artifactregistry.repositories.create] with:
... repositoryId: `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... format: `DOCKER`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... cleanupPolicyDryRun: `false` (active mode — eligible artifacts are deleted, not just logged)
... cleanupPolicies: a map keyed by policy ID with a single entry:
+
----
{
  "rb-delete-untagged": {
    "id": "rb-delete-untagged",
    "action": "DELETE",
    "condition": {
      "tagState": "UNTAGGED",
      "olderThan": "86400s"
    }
  }
}
----
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. NOTE: The cleanup policy underwrites the multi-platform contract documented in {rbtgo_image_delete}. V2 DELETE-by-tag against an OCI image index removes only the parent manifest, leaving per-platform children as untagged orphan content. GAR's cleanup background job (executes ~daily on Google's schedule, exact time unspecified) deletes manifests matching this policy on its next run; layer storage is reclaimed by GAR's separate daily layer-GC job. The 86400s (1-day) `olderThan` is measured from manifest creation time, not from when the manifest became untagged — orphans become eligible once they have existed in GAR for at least one day and are reaped on the next subsequent daily cleanup execution.
.. NOTE: REST schema verified against canonical sources. `cleanupPolicies` is a *map* keyed by policy ID, not an array — the gcloud CLI policy-file format used with `gcloud artifacts repositories set-cleanup-policies --policy=FILE` is a different (array, nested `{type: "Delete"}` action) schema that does not apply to this REST call. `action` is a *string enum* with values `ACTION_UNSPECIFIED | DELETE | KEEP`. `condition.tagState` enum values: `TAGGED | UNTAGGED | ANY`. `condition.olderThan` is a Duration-format string (seconds + `s` suffix). Maximum 10 cleanup policies per repository (this clause uses one). Schema sources for future re-verification:
... link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories[Repository resource reference] — `cleanupPolicies` and `cleanupPolicyDryRun` field shapes
... link:https://artifactregistry.googleapis.com/$discovery/rest?version=v1[Discovery document v1] — canonical CleanupPolicy / CleanupPolicyCondition schemas (authoritative for action enum values, condition field types)
... link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/repositories/cleanup-policy[Configure cleanup policies] — concept guide, daily-cadence statement, dry-run semantics

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_mason}
Service Account*:
.. NOTE: The
{rbtr_mason}
replaces Cloud Build's implicit service account to provide deterministic permissions and predictable authorization within the depot infrastructure.
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `mason-«RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... displayName: `«RBGC_DEPOT_DISPLAY_PREFIX» mason «RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«MASON_EMAIL»` from response `.email` field

//axhos_step
. *Configure
{rbtr_mason}
Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_repo} on `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/storage.objectViewer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} on `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/viewer`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/logging.logWriter`

//axhos_step
. *Enable Cloud Build service agent to impersonate
{rbtr_mason}*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on `«MASON_EMAIL»`
.. Add member: `serviceAccount:service-«PROJECT_NUMBER»@gcp-sa-cloudbuild.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
.. Grant role: `roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator`
.. NOTE: Cloud Build service agent is Google-provisioned (auto-created when Cloud Build API is enabled), not a user-created service account. The `tokenCreator` role enables build steps running as {rbtr_mason} (via the build JSON's `serviceAccount` field) to generate fresh access tokens for GCP API calls — required for GAR authentication (docker login, crane push). This is distinct from `serviceAccountUser` (actAs), which the {rbtr_director} holds on {rbtr_mason} for submitting builds.
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhos_step
. *Submit Per-Pool Probe Builds*:
.. For each worker pool variant in [`tether`, `airgap`]:
... {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/create[builds.create] with:
.... `serviceAccount`: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/serviceAccounts/«MASON_EMAIL»`
.... `options.pool.name`: full pool resource path for the variant
.... `options.logging`: `CLOUD_LOGGING_ONLY`
.... `steps[0]`: posture-check assertion (builder: `gcr.io/google.com/cloudsdktool/cloud-sdk:alpine`)
..... tether asserts `https://example.com` reachable AND `https://storage.googleapis.com` reachable (curl without `-f`; any HTTP response counts as reached)
..... airgap asserts `https://example.com` connection blocked AND `https://storage.googleapis.com` reachable
.... `steps[1]`: GAR write probe (builder: `gcr.io/cloud-builders/docker`) — `FROM scratch` image with a single marker file, pushed to `«REGION»-docker.pkg.dev/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/«GAR_REPOSITORY»/rbi_df/probe-«VARIANT»:probe`
... {rbbc_require}
submission returns HTTP 200/201 (build accepted). All other codes are fatal.
... {rbbc_await}
build terminal state via `builds.get` polled every `ZRBGP_BUILD_POLL_INTERVAL` seconds, with a `ZRBGP_BUILD_POLL_CEILING` ceiling (10 minutes total). SUCCESS is the expected terminal state on correct posture; FAILURE means the in-build assertion tripped (egress-posture mismatch) and operators investigate via the console link. Any other terminal state (CANCELLED / TIMEOUT / EXPIRED / INTERNAL_ERROR) indicates Cloud Build infrastructure trouble and is similarly diagnostic, not silently accepted.
... {rbbc_show}
per-pool probe block carrying the pool ID, GAR artifact reference, build ID + Cloud Build console link, and terminal status.
.. NOTE: Builder images are Google-hosted only (`gcr.io/...`). The airgap pool cannot reach `docker.io`; any non-Google builder would hang the build.
.. NOTE: Submission itself populates the per-pool concurrent-build quota row in Google's Cloud Build console UI — what the preflight diagnostic calls "after some build activity." A SUCCESS terminal probe confirms three things end-to-end: the pool can dispatch builds, the worker exhibits the egress posture stamped into its network config, and the worker can authenticate to GAR and push to `rbi_df`. Operators bump per-pool quota afterward via the now-populated console row to enable subsequent parallel gauntlet activity.
.. NOTE: Submission awaits terminal state inline. The two iterations of the loop run serially because the await blocks the loop body before the next submission; this is load-bearing. An earlier non-awaiting variant caused the late-clearing-probe-collision wedge — the airgap probe queued for ~19 minutes behind subsequent gauntlet dispatches, and when it finally cleared, the next tether conjure (e.g., `ordain_conjure_jupyter`) wedged in `QUEUED` until `queueTtl=3600s` expired the build. See `Memos/memo-20260517-cloudbuild-default-quota-wedge/`. The serialized await also makes the airgap probe's slot acquisition fast in the no-contention case, since no other gauntlet builds are competing during the levy window.
.. NOTE: In-build posture-assertion failure (e.g., airgap pool reaching the public internet, tether pool unable to resolve `storage.googleapis.com`) surfaces in the build's terminal status as FAILURE — a hard infra-drift signal. The posture-check script uses `curl` without `-f` so that HTTP 4xx/5xx responses from a reached server still count as "reached"; only honest network failures (DNS, connection refused, timeout) trip the assertion.
.. NOTE: The `rbi_df` namespace is a flat sibling of `rbi_hm` / `rbi_rq` / `rbi_es` under the GAR repository. {rbtgo_image_audit} / {rbtgo_image_rekon} enumerators ignore it by design — probe artifacts are operational, not part of the hallmark / reliquary / enshrine image catalogue. Filenames under `rbi_df` form a flat sea (no subdirs); each filename names one depot-scoped OCI artifact.

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Confirm Depot Creation*:
.. {rbbc_show}
single-line success banner naming `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` and the
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
follow-up hint

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Update Depot Tracking*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_depot_list_update}
to refresh per-moniker depot fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates depot infrastructure with configured build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool — all derived from `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
to create the
{rbtr_governor}
for this depot.

